verses.roman:
eka-saṅge dui jana kṣetre yabe āilā
rāmānanda rāya tabe prabhure mililā

synonyms: eka-saṅge—together; dui jana—these two persons; kṣetre—at Jagannātha-kṣetra (Jagannātha Purī); yabe—when; āilā—came back; rāmānanda rāya—Rāmānanda Rāya; tabe—at that time; prabhure—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; mililā—met.
translation: The King and Rāmānanda Rāya returned together to Jagannātha-kṣetra [Purī], and Śrī Rāmānanda Rāya met Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu.
